title: [Mistydeep, Northern Strand]
description: Tumbled from craggy hillsides now overgrown with trees, chunks of fractured shale and sandstone lie in jagged clumps along the west bank of the river.  A line of smaller rocks leads from the shore to one very large boulder that overlooks a particularly deep and clear section of river where large fish seem content to dwell.  As if to confirm the popularity of the site, fresh bear tracks and a few partially-eaten fish dot the surface of this particularly well-placed rock slab.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, southeast, south, northwest, down
room.location: the northern reaches of the Mistydeep River
